comment: Johnson (MIA) maintains his pivot foot at the end of his dribble.
Whiteside (MIA) is in the paint for longer than three seconds.
Gortat (WAS) maintains legal guarding position and makes incidental contact with Johnson (MIA) that does not affect his drive to the basket and shot attempt.
Whiteside (MIA) makes marginal contact with Oubre Jr. (WAS) on the screen.
Dragic (MIA) makes marginal contact with Oubre Jr. (WAS) that does not affect his ability to defend the play.
Gortat (WAS) sets the screen on Johnson (MIA) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
[Detectable with stop watch] Johnson (MIA) is in the paint without actively guarding an opponent for longer than three seconds.
Whiteside (MIA) makes incidental contact with Gortat (WAS) that does not affect his ability to defend the play.
Gortat (WAS) sets the screen on Johnson (MIA) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
[Observable in enhanced video] Beal (WAS) splits his feet on the perimeter.
Whiteside (MIA) sets the screen on Morris (WAS) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Gortat (WAS) and Whiteside (MIA) briefly engage with one another during rebounding.
Dragic (MIA) makes body to body contact with Beal (WAS) that affects his SQBR.
Johnson (MIA) makes contact with Wall (WAS) that affects his SQBR.
Morris (WAS) makes incidental contact with Johnson (MIA) that does not affect his SQBR.
Richardson (MIA) makes incidental contact with Wall (WAS) that does not affect his FOM.
Wall (WAS) commits a take foul on Richardson (MIA).
After communicating with the Replay Center, Wall (WAS) is assessed a common foul because it did not meet the criteria for a clear path foul.
Gortat (WAS) sets the screen on Johnson (MIA) and continues moving into him. Gortat also grabs Johnson's jersey.
Gortat (WAS) firms up his position and sets the screen on Johnson (MIA).
Whiteside (MIA) legally contests Beal (WAS) jump shot attempt. Any "high-five" contact after the release is considered incidental.
